END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260326T081800
DTEND:20260326T110600
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.903ft at 08:18\n-0.043ft at 11:06\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Nice mix of long-period SW swell and steep-angled\, shorter-period NW swel
 l sets up chest-shoulder-head high surf\, topping out mid day then easing 
 a bit during the afternoon when the swell starts to ease. Tide sensitive b
 reaks slowed by dawn patrol high tide\, then negative low tide mid day wil
 l be draining most areas. \n\nAt this point\, winds are looking to stay li
 ght all day for nice conditions. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260326T143000
DTEND:20260326T180600
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-0.027ft at 14:30\n-2.992ft at 18:06\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Nice mix of long-period SW swell and steep-angled\, shorter-period NW swel
 l sets up chest-shoulder-head high surf\, topping out mid day then easing 
 a bit during the afternoon when the swell starts to ease. Tide sensitive b
 reaks slowed by dawn patrol high tide\, then negative low tide mid day wil
 l be draining most areas. \n\nAt this point\, winds are looking to stay li
 ght all day for nice conditions. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260327T092400
DTEND:20260327T120600
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.941ft at 09:24\n-0.028ft at 12:06\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Easing blend of mid-period SW swell and shorter-period\, steep-angled NW s
 well for waves mainly running thigh to stomach high in the morning\, as be
 st combo breaks see better sets. Surf backs off a bit during the afternoon
  along with the fading swell. Dawn patrol is slowed by an early AM high ti
 de. Mid day gets drained by a negative low tide. \n\nLight/variable winds 
 due through the day\, keeping conditions fairly clean.
END:VEVENT
